Title: Policy Edit Primer (JSON rules, safety, and audit)

Purpose
- Standardize how admins edit governance policies (string or JSON).
- Ensure edits are validated, diffed, snapshotted, and audited in the Transactions ledger.

Policy Keys (examples)
- entity.allowed_roles      -> JSON list of strings (e.g., ["customer","resource","sponsor","staff","admin"])
- entity.resource_codes     -> JSON list of strings
- entity.us_states          -> JSON list of 2-letter codes (or string if you store CSV)

Golden Rules
1) Prefer JSON for lists/dicts; plain string for single scalar.
2) Validate JSON before saving; show a unified diff (current vs proposed).
3) Snapshot the DB before writing.
4) Save via governance service (policy_set) so it logs to the ledger.
5) Never store Python literals (True/None) — use strict JSON (true/null).

JSON Validation
- Accept either:
  - Valid JSON value (object/array/string/number/bool/null), OR
  - Plain string (fallback).
- If `json.loads(...)` succeeds → store as JSON; else store raw string.
- Minify for hashing; pretty-print for UI.

Diff Preview
- Use unified diff (difflib) of current_text vs proposed_text.
- Require explicit “Confirm & Save” after preview.

DB Snapshot (belt & suspenders)
- Take an online sqlite backup before applying the change.
- Keep last N snapshots in var/snapshots/ (optional cron to prune).

Audit Trail
- Use governance.services.policy_set(key=..., value=..., ptype="json"|"string", actor_id, request_id)
- Emit event: governance.policy.updated
- Put key + value in refs: {"policy_key": key, "value": value, "ptype": ptype}

Common Pitfalls
- Trailing commas or single quotes (invalid JSON).
- Accidentally storing JSON-encoded strings inside strings (double-encoding).
- Huge payloads: keep policies small; large catalogs belong in tables.

Quick Operator Flow (UI)
1) Paste/edit JSON.
2) Click “Preview Changes” → review diff.
3) Click “Confirm & Save” (creates snapshot → emits policy_set).
4) See success toast + ledger link.

Rollback
- Restore most recent DB snapshot (sqlite backup) OR
- Re-open editor, paste previous value from diff, save again.
